"cs.CV" (Computer Vision) is also likely, as the paper focuses on generating images and uses the CIFAR-10 dataset, which is commonly used in computer vision research. "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) is another possibility, as the paper discusses a neural network that can generate new images. "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility, as the paper discusses a neural network architecture. Finally, "cs.CL" (Computation and Language) is a less likely possibility, as the paper does not focus on natural language processing, but it does use a classifier to determine which training images are well reconstructed.
